      <p>
        I’m a product and category leader focused on building durable, high-performing consumer products in technically demanding categories.
      </p>

      <p>
        My background spans the full path from concept through manufacturing, distribution, and retail execution. I’ve worked across climbing, footwear, and mountain sports, with responsibility for strategy and performance across a ~$57MM global portfolio at Black Diamond Equipment.
      </p>

      <p>
        I don’t approach product as an isolated function. I see it as a system — where product decisions, margin structure, distribution, and operations all interact. The work is not just to build something excellent, but to ensure it survives scale, reaches the right customer, and performs in the market.
      </p>

      <h2>How I Work</h2>

      <p><strong>Concentrated bets outperform broad portfolios.</strong><br />
      Most organizations dilute effort across too many initiatives. I prioritize fewer, higher-upside programs and align teams around them.</p>

      <p><strong>Product must align with how it sells.</strong><br />
      Strong product is not enough. Distribution, retail context, and go-to-market execution are design constraints, not afterthoughts.</p>

      <p><strong>Exploration and execution require different modes.</strong><br />
      Early phases demand volatility and learning. Later phases require focus, discipline, and clarity. Knowing when to shift is critical.</p>

      <p><strong>Margin and structure matter.</strong><br />
      In mature, competitive markets, improvement comes from better allocation — simplifying SKU architecture, improving mix, and making hard portfolio decisions.</p>

      <h2>What I’ve Done</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Led product strategy and roadmap direction across climbing and footwear categories at Black Diamond Equipment.</li>
        <li>Stabilized revenue and market share in flat-to-declining markets while improving margin structure.</li>
        <li>Reduced SKU complexity by 15% to improve focus and efficiency.</li>
        <li>Reallocated resources toward core technical platforms by exiting lower-margin programs.</li>
        <li>Delivered product across multiple categories, from technical climbing equipment to performance footwear.</li>
      </ul>

